    "updated_at": "2015-08-06T15:51:47Z",
    "body": "@iamdriz you can make something that looks like a crappy copy sure, but then that means you have to use the transparent browser-window option which comes with _many_ drawbacks in Electron.\n\nHTML is great for all the stuff inside the bounds of the window - but not for outside the window, once you get into drawing fake shadows, fake borders, fake rounding edges, fake window controls it's a bad path to go down.\n\nThis new option could also be used on framed windows!\n"
  },
